== Open Questions from the Mixture-of-Superpositions Verification Protocol <sec:mos-questions>

A natural question is whether the verification guarantees of Caro et al. @Caro_2023 survive when the
quantum device itself is noisy (as opposed to the data-generating distribution in
@sec:agnostic-learning). Ma, Su, and Deng @Ma_2024 addressed this for the case of per-gate
depolarising noise applied independently to each gate in the quantum Fourier sampling circuit.
